  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[OS X Sleep and Hibernate]]></title>
    <link href="http://blog.mikeleon.com/blog/2009/01/30/osx-sleep-hibernate/"/>
    <updated>2009-01-30T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <id>http://blog.mikeleon.com/blog/2009/01/30/osx-sleep-hibernate</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class="entry-content"><h4>To view current hibernation mode: (default for portables is 3, desktops use 0)</h4>

<blockquote>

<p><code>pmset -g|grep hibernatemode</code></p>

</blockquote>

<h4>sleep (3): save to RAM, until low battery, then hibernate</h4>

<blockquote>

<p><code>sudo pmset -a hibernatemode 3</code></p>

</blockquote>

<h4>hibernate (1): save directly to disk, consumes no power (can even remove battery?)</h4>

<blockquote>

<p><code><b>sudo pmset -a hibernatemode 1</b></code></p>

</blockquote>

<h4><b>hibernation disabled (0): goes to sleep, dies without power</b></h4>

<blockquote>

<p><code><b><b>sudo pmset -a hibernatemode 0 </b></b></code></p>

</blockquote>
</div>
]]></content>
